This was done circa 23 April, 2010, after doing Ruby and BDD for only a couple of months.

It was also done as part of a code retreat, where I was really digging blabbing and demonstrating how cool Cucumber and RSpec was. The code was written under the usual duress of the timer...

...and it shows <g>. I'll try to clean it up one of these days.

You can simply start playing by typing
  bin/gol
and pressing Enter.

A board size of 10 doesn't last too long before it reaches a static equilibrium.

A size of 25 seems to got very long. You might get bored and need to do 
	Ctrl-C

You can also run the cucumber features...
